Last year, for the first time, Mr. Croatti joined the list of the 200 best-paid chief executives in the United States, according to an annual ranking done by Equilar for The New York Times. He made the list because of a large stock award that pushed the value of his 2016 pay package to $17.69 million.

Advertisement

Continue reading the main story

Ronald Daniel Croatti was born on April 20, 1943, in Boston. His mother was the former Alba Olney. His paternal grandparents had emigrated from Rimini, Italy, in 1909.Mr. Croatti was 14 when he began working, on and off, at UniFirst. At that time, the company was called National Overall Dry Cleaning Company. He was hired officially in 1965, not long after he graduated from San Diego State University.Besides his sons Michael and Matthew and his sister, he is survived by his wife, Carol; another son, Aldo; a daughter, Melissa; and nine grandchildren.In the “Undercover Boss” episode, Mr. Croatti mentioned that he was grooming his son Michael, a senior vice president, to succeed him. But Cynthia Croatti said no decision had been made as to who would become chief executive.One of the first items of business for his successor may be the company’s growing competition. Its main rival, Cintas, recently acquired another uniform rental company, G&K Services, to create a company with an estimated $6 billion in revenue. (UniFirst has also grown through acquisitions, adding Arrow Uniform, a Michigan-based company, in a $122 million deal last year.)Ms. Croatti said she had been impressed by her brother’s appearance on “Undercover Boss.”“He was extremely comfortable in front of the cameras,” she said. “He could have been an actor.”
